{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"Hello,\\nI just noticed that there are 3 bacteria have this term, which is being given by PANTHER;\\nGO:0070478 nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, 3'-5' exonucleolytic nonsense-mediated decay\\nAs bacteria do not have nuclei, nor NMD, this term makes no sense. \\n\\nCan you add the following please? Any other terms related to non-mediated RNA decay should also have this constraint.\\nnever in taxon: 2\\n\\nThanks, Andrea\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7uwLXh\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Added in the 'only_in_taxon' file: \\n\\nGO:0141065\\tmaternal mRNA clearance\\tNCBITaxon:2759\\tEukaryota\\t\\nGO:0000958\\tmitochondrial mRNA catabolic process\\tNCBITaxon:2759\\tEukaryota\\t\\nGO:0000956\\tnuclear-transcribed\\tmRNA catabolic process\\tNCBITaxon:2759\\tEukaryota\\t\\n\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-05T14:49:36Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31670#issuecomment-4005606881\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"Taxon constraint: please add for GO:0070478 and similar terms\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31670\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
